   "body" : "This PR allows the double negation syntax (`-nofoo=0`) only for pure boolean args.\r\n\r\nOn master, `-nodebuglogfile=0` creates a log file named `1`.\r\n\r\nWith this PR:\r\n```\r\n$ src/bitcoind -nodebuglogfile=0\r\nError: Error parsing command line arguments: Double-negative -nodebuglogfile=0 is not allowed\r\n$ src/bitcoind -nowallet=0\r\nError: Error parsing command line arguments: Double-negative -nowallet=0 is not allowed\r\n```\r\n\r\nNOTES for reviewers:\r\n- this PR is based on top of #16097, so only the last three commits are to be reviewed here\r\n- the related #16476 should be based on this PR\r\n- it seems no release notes are required, since provided behavior has already been stated in the [release notes for 0.6.0](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/doc/release-notes/release-notes-0.6.0.md):\r\n> The `-nolisten`, `-noupnp` and `-nodnsseed` command-line options were renamed to `-listen`, `-upnp` and `-dnsseed`, with a default value of `1`. The old names are still supported for compatibility (so specifying `-nolisten` is automatically interpreted as `-listen=0`; every boolean argument can now be specified as either `-foo` or `-nofoo`).",
